          "model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
          "code": "import sys\ninput = sys.stdin.readline\n\nt = int(input())\nfor _ in range(t):\n    x, y = map(int, input().split())\n    if x <= y:\n        q = y // x\n        print((y + q * x) // 2)\n    else:\n        # When x > y, swap roles: find n such that n mod x = y mod n\n        # Use lcm-based approach: n = lcm(x, y) / 2\n        # Actually, use the same formula but with x and y swapped conceptually\n        # n mod x = y mod n means n = k*x + r and y = n + r for some r\n        # So y - n = n - k*x => y = 2n - k*x => n = (y + k*x)/2\n        # We need n > y (so that y mod n = y), and n mod x = y\n        # If y < x, then we want n mod x = y, so n = k*x + y for some k\n        # and y mod n = y (since y < n), so n mod x = y mod n = y\n        # smallest such n > y: k = 1, n = x + y\n        # but we need n mod x = y, which means (x + y) mod x = y mod x = y (since y < x)\n        # This works when y < x\n        print(x + y)",
